Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:02:00.80,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who would sink to becoming a dog of the military is unworthy of being taught even the basics of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:04.81,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy should be used for the benefit of the masses. Isn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:13.57,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}Master, we're currently under threat from neighboring countries. We're in an urgent need to strengthen our forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.94,0:02:16.40,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is essential for protecting the people-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.40,0:02:18.36,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of hearing that same excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.49,0:02:27.41,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't sit here and watch this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:32.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Someone as talented as you suffering crushing poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:34.42,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Please become a State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:36.67,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, you'll be able to conduct other experiments-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.67,0:02:39.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I've already completed my experiments long in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.47,0:02:41.89,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.72,0:02:45.64,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The most powerful alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:49.06,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Though depending on how it's used, it could be the most deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:51.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I perfected it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:54.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,...and became satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:03.66,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are creatures who must continually strive toward the truth as long as they are alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.12,0:03:08.45,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They die as soon as they stop the process of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.08,0:03:12.50,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I had already died long in the past-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:14.29,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:18.51,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.51,0:03:19.42,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Master Hawkeye!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:22.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Take care... of my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.30,0:03:28.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Every detail of my experiment... is with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:42.61,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for having to rely on you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:44.28,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.28,0:03:46.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,It's my duty as a former student.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.37,0:03:50.79,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hesitate to visit me at the military if anything happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.12,0:03:58.05,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you also going to judge me for becoming a soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.55,0:04:02.51,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,As everyone may say, there is a chance I'll end up dying like a piece of trash out on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:10.64,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But even then, if it means I'll be able to protect this country, I don't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.10,0:04:15.02,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry if I'm boring you. It's a childish dream of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:17.23,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:19.65,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's quite admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:23.90,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,A future where everyone will be able to live in happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:26.16,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Can I trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:30.99,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Can I entrust you with Father's dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.34,0:04:45.30,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Hayate. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:48.22,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:50.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine... It happens a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:53.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.10,0:04:54.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant to the Führer President?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.73,0:04:56.90,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:02.28,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you had a rough time out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.82,0:05:04.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't shoot anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.24,0:05:06.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:12.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No... I couldn't bring myself to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:16.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:20.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm not prepared, I end up troubling others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.84,0:05:23.21,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:28.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar was the one who killed Winry's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:35.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I had a horrible feeling in my gut at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:38.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,In my mind, the gun suddenly turned into something horrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:40.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And when I realized it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.28,0:05:47.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I think she despised Scar enough to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:50.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never seen her cry as much as she did after he left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.41,0:05:54.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:58.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand her feelings at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:02.17,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You can only worry about something like that because you came back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:05.51,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,But you have to survive...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.21,0:06:08.13,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,...for the sake of the people important to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.51,0:06:10.76,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You have to protect her, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:14.64,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You love Winry, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! I-I-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:22.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,S-She's just a childhood friend of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.11,0:06:23.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just like family!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:26.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,P-Protecting her is nothing out of the ordinary!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:26.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:27.65,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.40,0:06:31.49,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like this was a burden on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:40.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever thought of it as a burden?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.50,0:06:46.59,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even have the right to complain about its weight anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:51.01,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I've taken the lives of many people in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.59,0:06:56.26,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm also the one who chose this path.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:06:59.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Are you referring to Ishbal?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.52,0:07:04.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if I ask you about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.57,0:07:11.28,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Let me hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.74,0:07:15.28,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,What did you wretches do in Ishbal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:20.79,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Ishbal was a rough place to live, full of rocks and sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.37,0:07:28.96,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,So it's only fitting that a strict religion and\Na tenacious race of people reside there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.46,0:07:36.30,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,But some people were unhappy\Nthat they were annexed to Amestris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.39,0:07:38.72,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,And just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:49.61,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Because of one bullet, the unhappiness evolved into anger and spread throughout Ishbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.36,0:07:59.70,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The riot turned into a civil war and continued on for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.37,0:08:06.04,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one document decided everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:09.71,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Executive Order No. 3066.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.30,0:08:13.34,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It began the Ishbal Extermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.05,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Just that one sheet of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:34.61,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It was a living hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:38.87,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The air was choked with the stench of rotting corpses and gunpowder,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:42.04,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,and the sand was soaked with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:55.09,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,An infantryman could fire at random, and if lucky, he might hit someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:57.39,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,But sniping is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.72,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,When you pull the trigger, someone dies for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:05.73,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The two groups who were the most closely related in terms of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:07.10,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,...would be snipers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.69,0:09:11.07,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,...and State Alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:18.24,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Basque Gran, the Iron Blood Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:20.20,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Iron and Blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:22.62,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Weapons and Soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:27.79,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Who else would be more fitting to stand at the forefront?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:06.91,Default,Koma,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:08.50,Default,Koma,0000,0000,0000,,Ishbalan brats!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:11.84,Default,Koma,0000,0000,0000,,How... How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.59,0:10:15.30,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Roy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.80,0:10:17.01,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Roy Mustang!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:22.72,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,So you were here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.72,0:10:24.22,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:25.56,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,But man,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.85,0:10:27.93,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,your eyes look different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:32.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Same with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.19,0:10:34.86,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We all have the eyes of murderers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:37.07,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.74,0:10:44.37,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we all talk about the future of this country at the military academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:45.33,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:48.08,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,A beautiful future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:50.62,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, a letter for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:52.58,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.75,0:10:55.30,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:56.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.25,0:10:58.21,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,My beautiful future!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:00.26,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Her name's Gracia!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:04.14,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,She's waiting for my return in Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.10,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:10.52,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,What if other guys hit on her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:15.44,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no way Gracia would cheat on a handsome guy like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:17.07,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.07,0:11:19.78,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes, let me warn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:22.86,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,This happens a lot in both movies and novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.32,0:11:26.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The guy who talks about his lover on a battlefield...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.03,0:11:27.12,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...ends up dying right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.91,0:11:29.41,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:36.13,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,This is what keeps me alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:41.72,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,This letter, and this letter only, lets me dream of tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:45.64,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,In this war that may never end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:49.27,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. There's no telling when this war will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:55.90,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many troops the country deploys, the desert just absorbs them like water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:12:00.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We suffer, conquer, and what's left?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:02.65,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing but sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.65,0:12:07.24,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's far too big of an operation for it to merely be suppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:15.08,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Major Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:17.59,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.17,0:12:19.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,How terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.09,0:12:21.09,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,This woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.84,0:12:23.80,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...now also bears the eyes of murderers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.81,0:12:36.56,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me, Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:41.78,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Soldiers are supposed to protect the people. Why are we killing them instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.90,0:12:48.28,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is supposed to bring people happiness. Why is it being used for murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.41,0:12:53.16,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's the State Alchemists' job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:12:57.92,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Why are soldiers killing the people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.92,0:13:01.05,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's what we were ordered to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:03.13,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:06.76,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling us to look at this horrible scene rationally?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:10.22,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... for example...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.47,0:13:15.89,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Girl, your face has the expression of "I'm doing this against my will".
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:21.98,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Can you say for certain that there hasn't been a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:27.74,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,...when you successfully sniped your enemy and felt good about your skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.11,0:13:29.37,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Sniper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.99,0:13:31.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:36.41,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,From my point of view, it's you all who can't be understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:39.29,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,A battlefield is a place for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.29,0:13:44.80,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Did you put on that uniform\Nwithout being prepared to kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.55,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look away from death. Look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:54.31,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,When you kill, face them directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:56.81,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,And don't forget them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:13:59.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Your enemies will never forget you either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.61,0:14:04.82,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.32,0:14:07.11,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I need to head off to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.36,0:14:09.78,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:11.66,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Later, Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:12.66,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:15.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:18.62,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:21.92,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.67,Default,Hugh,0000,0000,0000,,Reasons are always simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:35.77,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Then what is the reason behind this war?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.23,0:14:38.35,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,There...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:42.40,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,...was a reason. A horrible reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:20.27,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You created a philosopher's stone using our blood?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.27,0:15:22.27,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do with that stone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:26.15,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,It went to the hands of Major Zolf J. Kimblee...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:28.86,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,...the Crimson Alchemist...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:33.78,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,The man with cold eyes...\Nwho has his long black hair tied back?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:34.87,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:37.45,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.66,0:15:41.12,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,What else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.12,0:15:45.75,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The war situation changed with just one intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:51.01,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Such beautiful sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.42,0:15:55.64,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Such wondrous sounds ringing throughout my body...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:16:00.14,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,My spinal cord dances with sadness. My eardrum shivers with joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.14,0:16:07.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,This feeling can only be achieved here, where we lay so close to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.36,0:16:11.53,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful career!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:20.62,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,A beautiful sound!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.62,0:16:24.50,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! The philosopher's stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:32.92,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a matter of time before the extermination was complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.09,0:16:42.77,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,And then, the Ishbalan priest of highest rank, Roug Roa, stood before the Führer President to save his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.81,0:16:44.94,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:50.65,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,So you want me to trade the lives of the tens of thousands of Ishbalans in exchange for your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:52.78,Default,Roug,0000,0000,0000,,Correct. I'm-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.78,0:16:53.95,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be conceited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:17:00.37,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to say that your life is worth just as much as the lives of the ones who are left?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.33,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get ahead of yourself, human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:07.92,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A person's life is worth as much as anyone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.92,0:17:10.59,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,No more, no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:12.42,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I won't accept the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.42,0:17:13.92,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Nor will I call off the extermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.92,0:17:15.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:16.97,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,God will smite you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:18.93,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,"God"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.93,0:17:21.01,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,How strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:25.23,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,After all this, I've yet to be smote.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.98,0:17:30.98,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,How many more Ishbalans must I kill for that to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:32.69,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:38.99,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,God is only a figure created by humans;\Nthat's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:47.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to bring an iron hammer down on me,\Ndo it yourself without having to rely on God, human!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:56.01,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually, the war ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.47,0:17:59.89,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,and we were allowed to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.80,0:18:04.64,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we soldiers are nothing but trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.85,0:18:06.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.06,0:18:09.19,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,One human only has the power to do so much. {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:12.98,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm going to protect... {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.82,0:18:15.49,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...even if it's just a handful of them... {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:17.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...the ones most important to me. {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:21.70,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,A subordinate protects their subordinate, and so forth. {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:25.62,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That should be possible, even for us puny humans. {ep10}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.26,0:18:49.06,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,So you decided to take this path,\Neven after what you experienced in Ishbal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:50.39,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:55.94,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,If this world is based on the concept of\Nequivalent exchange, as stated in alchemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:19:05.74,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,then we must carry corpses and cross the river of blood in exchange for the new generation to live in happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.04,0:19:12.08,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm appointing you as my assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:15.13,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to protect my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.34,0:19:18.59,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.59,0:19:23.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm leaving you in charge of defending my back,\Nit means you can shoot me from behind at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:27.72,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If I ever stray from my path,\Nshoot me right away with those hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.39,0:19:30.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You have that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:32.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Will you follow me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.90,0:19:35.27,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:38.03,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish, I will follow you to the depths of Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:49.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But even if the Colonel becomes the Führer, it wouldn't change the militaristic element of this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:51.00,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.00,0:19:54.21,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Congress pretty much exists as the army's puppet right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.21,0:19:57.80,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Someone would need to change that and turn this country into a democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.55,0:20:04.09,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,For this country to be reborn, all the faults that existed from the militaristic regime will have to be brushed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:05.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Faults?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:12.06,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx92}For example, the government may have to pass judgment on those who committed atrocities during the Ishbal Extermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:14.85,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.85,0:20:19.73,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,The heroes during the troubled times are nothing but mass murderers during times of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.73,0:20:22.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So the Colonel is reaching for the top while knowing about all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.65,0:20:25.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's only on a path of self-destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.24,0:20:30.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The Homunculi are the ones who were pulling the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:35.83,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Homunculi were the ones who triggered it,\Nwe're the ones who committed the atrocities.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:39.63,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't turn away from death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:42.80,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't forget the ones we killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.80,0:20:43.72,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.43,0:20:48.60,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,...they'll never forget us, the ones who killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.85,0:20:50.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.43,0:20:56.56,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have something to do before you start worrying about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:21:00.40,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and Alphonse need to return to your bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.40,0:21:05.20,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure a lot of people are waiting for the day you reach your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.82,0:21:08.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.03,0:21:12.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely get my body back. Together with Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:16.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for letting us stay, Dr. Nox.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.96,0:21:19.09,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... Mister Armor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.34,0:21:23.84,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Really, thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:27.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have a name, you know. It's Alphonse Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:28.97,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Elric?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.35,0:21:31.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You remember Edward Elric, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:33.81,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That small alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:35.77,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm his younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:39.15,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my body due to certain circumstances, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:41.90,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,If you're that guy's younger brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.90,0:21:43.94,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...does this mean you look just like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.94,0:21:44.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:48.45,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm much taller than him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.45,0:21:52.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My face isn't that stern, and I'm much stronger than him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.29,0:21:54.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not short-tempered, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.04,0:21:55.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a gentleman!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.66,0:21:59.17,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.33,0:22:02.92,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you get your body back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.71,0:22:06.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I hope so, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:41.02,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh, I've brought your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:45.36,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's awfully quiet in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.61,0:23:49.11,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be you're crying again, reminiscing about Ishbal?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.66,0:24:01.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The White Devil has been released into the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.54,0:24:04.67,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The new fight begins now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.67,0:24:06.96,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But the boy will not flinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.21,0:24:10.84,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,He gets up and walks again, with hope as his landmark.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.42,0:24:15.80,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:20.56,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 31, The 520 Cens Promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.72,0:24:25.60,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The world which can only be understood by the ones who fought together is right in front of us.
